(Momoko) Huh?

212
00:12:15,368 --> 00:12:18,805
(Minseok) In Korea, it's called "Yunseul."

213
00:12:18,872 --> 00:12:23,310
The surface of water that sparkles when it catches the light.

214
00:12:23,376 --> 00:12:25,312
(Momoko) Hey.

215
00:12:25,378 --> 00:12:27,314
That sparkle →

216
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:31,384
Someone wanted to give it a special name.

217
00:12:35,388 --> 00:12:37,824
(Momoko) Something...

218
00:12:37,891 --> 00:12:39,326
(Minseok) Huh?

219
00:12:39,392 --> 00:12:43,330
(Momoko) I think I might say something a little harsh.

220
00:12:43,396 --> 00:12:48,335
Me like today →

221
00:12:48,401 --> 00:12:54,841
I want to protect the clinic as a place where someone can feel safe.

222
00:12:54,908 --> 00:12:58,912
(Minseok) Is it a dream? Momoko's.

223
00:13:00,413 --> 00:13:02,916
(Momoko) It's a dream.

224
00:13:06,353 --> 00:13:09,789
(Momoko) Do you have one too, Minseok? dream.

225
00:13:09,856 --> 00:13:12,792
(Minseok) I...

226
00:13:12,859 --> 00:13:18,865
>> Korean

227
00:13:26,873 --> 00:13:29,809
(Minseok) I am →

228
00:13:29,876 --> 00:13:35,382
I want to create a hotel that inherits the wishes of my father, who raised me.

229
00:13:36,883 --> 00:13:38,885
(Momoko) A wonderful dream.

230
00:13:40,387 --> 00:13:44,324
(Minseok) Ever since I came to Japan, I didn't know what my dreams were →

231
00:13:44,391 --> 00:13:49,329
I think I remembered it when I was talking to Momoko.

232
00:13:49,396 --> 00:13:51,831
(Momoko) It's all thanks to the glitter.

233
00:13:51,898 --> 00:13:53,900
Yunsul.

234
00:13:57,404 --> 00:14:00,407
(Momoko) I will support Minseok's dream.

235
00:14:02,409 --> 00:14:07,347
(Minseok) I will also support Momoko-san's dream.

236
00:14:09,349 --> 00:14:11,351
(Momoko) Hehehe...｡

237
00:14:22,462 --> 00:14:24,397
(Momoko) Wow! I was surprised!

238
00:14:24,464 --> 00:14:26,900
What… >> Date?

239
00:14:26,967 --> 00:14:31,404
(Momoko) Huh? No, no, it's not like that.

240
00:14:31,471 --> 00:14:33,473
>> Hmm.

241
00:14:34,908 --> 00:14:36,843
That outfit is cute.

242
00:14:36,910 --> 00:14:38,845
(Momoko) Really? Isn't it weird?

243
00:14:38,912 --> 00:14:41,348
>> Hey, I was drinking until the other morning →

244
00:14:41,414 --> 00:14:43,416
Are you really friends?

245
00:14:44,918 --> 00:14:46,419
(Momoko) Yes, but.

246
00:14:48,421 --> 00:14:51,358
I don't need dinner today.

247
00:14:51,424 --> 00:14:53,927
Well then, I'll go.

248
00:14:56,429 --> 00:14:59,866
Minseok-san, sorry for keeping you waiting.

249
