(Minseok) No, it's really cute.

250
00:15:02,936 --> 00:15:06,873
(Momoko) Woohoo Thank you.

251
00:15:06,940 --> 00:15:08,942
Shall we go? (Minseok) Yes.

252
00:15:10,443 --> 00:15:12,379
(Momoko) Minseok looks good in white too.

253
00:15:12,445 --> 00:15:14,447
(Minseok) Ah, thank you.

254
00:15:19,452 --> 00:15:21,955
>> Are you bad at lying?

255
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:30,463
(Momoko) Hmm! It feels good.

256
00:15:32,465 --> 00:15:34,834
(Minseok) It reminds me of the Han River.

257
00:15:34,901 --> 00:15:37,337
(Momoko) Han River?

258
00:15:37,404 --> 00:15:40,840
(Minseok) I often took walks along the Han River with my father.

259
00:15:40,907 --> 00:15:42,842
With my brother.

260
00:15:42,909 --> 00:15:44,344
(Momoko) Hmm.

261
00:15:44,411 --> 00:15:47,347
(Minseok) I'll show you around when I come to Korea. (Momoko) Whoa.

262
00:15:47,414 --> 00:15:50,850
(Minseok) Ah, Samcheong Dong-gil and Naksang Kong-won →

263
00:15:50,917 --> 00:15:52,852
Also, Hannam-dong.

264
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:54,854
I think it would be fun if we went together.

265
00:15:54,921 --> 00:15:57,857
(Momoko) Hannamdo...? (Minseok) Hannam-dong.

266
00:15:57,924 --> 00:16:00,860
There are also many stylish cafes and galleries.

267
00:16:00,927 --> 00:16:02,862
(Momoko) Hmm, did you go there often?

268
00:16:02,929 --> 00:16:06,866
(Minseok) Oh no, actually never.

269
00:16:06,933 --> 00:16:09,369
(Momoko) Huh? Is that so?

270
00:16:09,436 --> 00:16:14,441
(Minseok) If Momoko is here, I'd like to go to various places.

271
00:16:17,944 --> 00:16:20,880
(Momoko) Hey, would you like to stop going to the movies today?

272
00:16:20,947 --> 00:16:22,382
(Minseok) Why?

273
00:16:22,449 --> 00:16:26,886
(Momoko) Let's make today the day for Minseok to do what he wants.

274
00:16:26,953 --> 00:16:28,888
(Minseok) But...

275
00:16:28,955 --> 00:16:31,891
(Momoko) What kind of things does Minseok like?→

276
00:16:31,958 --> 00:16:34,327
I want to know.

277
00:16:34,394 --> 00:16:36,396
(Minseok) Really?

278
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:45,905
(Minseok) Then there's one thing I wanted to try.

279
00:16:53,413 --> 00:16:55,849
(Momoko) Maybe →

280
00:16:55,915 --> 00:16:58,351
Have you never eaten cup ramen?

281
00:16:58,418 --> 00:17:00,854
(Minseok) Hehe, there it is.

282
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:02,856
(Momoko) But what I want to do is...

283
00:17:02,922 --> 00:17:04,858
(Minseok) A standard Korean date.

284
00:17:04,924 --> 00:17:08,862
It's popular to eat ramen together along the Han River.

285
00:17:08,928 --> 00:17:10,864
(Momoko) Hey.

286
00:17:10,930 --> 00:17:12,866
Looks delicious.

287
00:17:12,932 --> 00:17:22,876
♪～

288
00:17:22,942 --> 00:17:24,878
(Minseok) Please.

289
00:17:24,944 --> 00:17:27,380
(Momoko) Huh? (Minseok) On a serving plate.

290
00:17:27,447 --> 00:17:29,382
(Momoko) Amazing.

291
00:17:29,449 --> 00:17:31,384
(Minseok) Would you like to do this in Japan? this.

292
00:17:31,451 --> 00:17:32,886
(Momoko) I saw it for the first time.

293
00:17:32,952 --> 00:17:34,888
I'll enjoy having this.

294
00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:41,828
yeah? It's more delicious than usual.

295
00:17:41,895 --> 00:17:43,897
(Minseok) Itadakimasu.

296
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:48,401
(Momoko) What do you think?

297
00:17:50,904 --> 00:17:54,407
(Minseok) One of my dreams has come true.

298
00:17:55,909 --> 00:17:57,844
(Momoko) Can I have a bite of Minseok's?

299
00:17:57,911 --> 00:18:00,413
(Minseok) Ah, of course let's share. (Momoko) Yes.

300
00:18:08,922 --> 00:18:11,858
(Mizushima) Please take your time and enjoy your stay.

301
00:18:11,925 --> 00:18:14,360
(Male) Thank you.

302
00:18:14,427 --> 00:18:16,863
Mr. Shinkai.

303
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:19,866
It's been a long time. (Eri) Hello.

304
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:21,935
What's it like today?

305
00:18:23,937 --> 00:18:26,372
I want to try this afternoon tea.

306
00:18:26,439 --> 00:18:29,375
(Mizushima) Thank you as always.

307
00:18:29,442 --> 00:18:31,377
Isn't Minseok here?

308
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:32,879
(Mizushima) Ah...｡

309
00:18:32,946 --> 00:18:37,383
Kim Min Seok is taking a day off today.

310
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:40,887
Do you have any suggestions?

311
00:18:40,954 --> 00:18:43,957
No, it's okay.

312
00:18:46,459 --> 00:18:49,896
(Momoko) I wonder what kind of hotel it is.

313
00:18:49,963 --> 00:18:52,398
(Minseok) Huh?

314
00:18:52,465 --> 00:18:56,970
(Momoko) This is the dream hotel that Minseok wants to create.

315
00:19:00,473 --> 00:19:04,911
(Minseok) The hotel I want to build is →

316
00:19:04,978 --> 00:19:10,917
It's like the customer has returned to their second home →

317
00:19:10,984 --> 00:19:13,419
It's that kind of hotel.

318
00:19:13,486 --> 00:19:16,990
(Momoko) Another home?

319
00:19:18,491 --> 00:19:23,930
(Minseok) There are various circumstances for people who come to stay at a hotel.

320
00:19:23,997 --> 00:19:26,933
For those traveling from overseas→

321
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:31,938
People coming from rural areas to attend ceremonial occasions for loved ones →

322
00:19:32,005 --> 00:19:34,374
For those who want to reward themselves→

323
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:39,379
Some people are happy, some are sad, and some are anxious.

324
00:19:39,445 --> 00:19:41,381
(Momoko) Yes.

325
00:19:41,447 --> 00:19:44,884
(Minseok) I care about any customer→

326
00:19:44,951 --> 00:19:47,387
Feel safe when you return to the hotel →

327
00:19:47,453 --> 00:19:51,391
Feel like relaxing in another home →

328
00:19:51,457 --> 00:19:55,461
I want to create a place like that...

329
00:20:00,466 --> 00:20:02,402
(Minseok) It might be impossible though.

330
00:20:02,468 --> 00:20:05,405
(Momoko) It's not impossible.

331
00:20:05,471 --> 00:20:07,974
I'm sure it will come true.

332
00:20:11,978 --> 00:20:15,982
(Momoko) Aren't our dreams similar?

333
00:20:18,484 --> 00:20:24,490
Min-seok also wants to create a place where someone can feel safe.

334
00:20:27,994 --> 00:20:29,996
(Minseok) Maybe so.

335
00:20:32,498 --> 00:20:36,436
(Momoko) I have to make that dream come true.

336
00:20:39,439 --> 00:20:40,873
(Minseok) Yes.

337
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:55,455
♪～

338
00:20:58,458 --> 00:21:00,393
>> Take it out. (Mika) Huh?

339
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:02,462
Eri-san.

340
00:21:03,963 --> 00:21:06,899
Hello. >> What's the matter?

341
00:21:06,966 --> 00:21:10,903
Oh, I happened to be passing by.

342
00:21:10,970 --> 00:21:12,405
How is everyone doing?

343
00:21:12,472 --> 00:21:14,407
Shall I stop by? Even if I say →

344
00:21:14,474 --> 00:21:17,410
Min-seok-san also left, so the director and I are the only ones left.

345
00:21:17,477 --> 00:21:21,914
📱(vibration sound)

346
00:21:21,981 --> 00:21:25,418
Ah, Yabba, Momo-chan-sensei also had a day off today, so it was tough.

347
00:21:25,485 --> 00:21:27,487
Sorry again.

348
00:21:29,989 --> 00:21:33,493
(Mizushima) [Kim Min-seok is taking a day off today]

349
00:21:35,428 --> 00:21:36,929
📱(vibration sound)

350
00:21:42,435 --> 00:21:47,940
Korean

351
00:21:53,446 --> 00:21:55,882
(Minseok) I'll eat it. (Momoko) I'll eat it.

352
00:21:55,948 --> 00:21:58,885
(Minseok) Mmm, it's sweet. (Momoko) Delicious.

353
00:21:58,951 --> 00:22:01,387
(Minseok) I wanted to try something like this.

354
00:22:01,454 --> 00:22:03,389
Eating while walking.

355
00:22:03,456 --> 00:22:05,391
(Momoko) Have you never done it in Korea?

356
00:22:05,458 --> 00:22:08,394
(Minseok) Ah... my mother didn't like it.

357
00:22:08,461 --> 00:22:12,899
(Momoko) Hmm, is your mother strict?

358
00:22:12,965 --> 00:22:14,901
(Minseok) That's tough...

359
00:22:14,967 --> 00:22:17,904
(Momoko) Ah, if you don't want to answer, then absolutely.

360
00:22:17,970 --> 00:22:23,409
(Minseok) My mother suddenly decided to accept me from Japan→

361
00:22:23,476 --> 00:22:26,412
She must have been desperate as a mother.

362
00:22:26,479 --> 00:22:28,414
(Momoko) I see.

363
00:22:28,481 --> 00:22:30,416
(Minseok) But my brother and I have always been close.

364
00:22:30,483 --> 00:22:32,418
(Momoko) Are you still in touch?

365
00:22:32,485 --> 00:22:35,855
(Minseok) Ah... now.

366
00:22:35,922 --> 00:22:39,358
(Roller coaster running sound)

367
00:22:39,425 --> 00:22:42,929
(Momoko) Ah, hey, would you like to ride that?

368
00:22:45,431 --> 00:22:46,933
(Minseok) Huh?

369
00:22:49,435 --> 00:22:51,938
(Momoko) Wow! (Minseok) Ah!

370
00:23:01,781 --> 00:23:03,549
(Momoko) I'm coming.

371
00:23:06,319 --> 00:23:08,254
What is it? What is it?

372
00:23:08,321 --> 00:23:12,759
Oh so cute!

373
00:23:12,825 --> 00:23:14,761
Let's do it again.

374
00:23:14,827 --> 00:23:16,763
(Minseok) Huh? One more time? (Momoko) One more time!

375
00:23:16,829 --> 00:23:19,265
I'll keep doing it until I get the same one.

376
00:23:19,332 --> 00:23:22,769
(Sound of putting money in)

377
00:23:22,835 --> 00:23:26,272
(Momoko) Well, I've been looking for it all day, and where do you think it came from?

378
00:23:26,339 --> 00:23:29,776
(Minseok) Eh, where is it? Ah, I see. Above your head?

379
00:23:29,842 --> 00:23:32,779
(Momoko) Ah, I've done that before, but it's different.

380
00:23:32,845 --> 00:23:34,714
What a refrigerator!

381
00:23:34,781 --> 00:23:37,216
(Minseok) Huh? They're glasses, right? (Momoko) That's right.

382
00:23:37,283 --> 00:23:39,218
I put my glasses in the fridge.

383
00:23:39,285 --> 00:23:41,721
(Minseok) Momoko-san is unexpectedly outstanding.

384
00:23:41,788 --> 00:23:45,725
(Momoko) There are about 10 more stories like this hahaha.

385
00:23:45,792 --> 00:24:12,752
♪～

386
00:24:12,819 --> 00:24:18,758
📱(vibration sound)

387
00:24:18,825 --> 00:24:20,760
(Momoko) What is it? 📱(Vibration sound)

388
00:24:20,827 --> 00:24:22,762
(Minseok) The sooner you get out, the better. 📱(Vibration sound)

389
00:24:22,829 --> 00:24:24,764
(Momoko) Yeah. 📱(Vibration sound)

390
00:24:24,831 --> 00:24:26,766
(Momoko) Hello. 📱 (Mika) Ah, Momo-chan-sensei?

391
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:29,268
(Momoko) Yeah. 📱 The director suddenly collapsed.

392
00:24:29,335 --> 00:24:31,838
(Momoko) Yeah, I understand. I'll go right away.

393
00:24:36,108 --> 00:24:37,610
(Peach) Dean.

394
00:24:39,612 --> 00:24:41,547
Director, how is your condition?

395
00:24:41,614 --> 00:24:43,549
(Takuto) I'm calm.

396
00:24:43,616 --> 00:24:46,552
He seemed tired, so I put in an IV drip just in case.

397
00:24:46,619 --> 00:24:50,056
(Mika) I was really nervous, Momo-chan, the teacher wasn't there either.

398
00:24:50,122 --> 00:24:54,560
No, I'm sorry, I suddenly went crazy.

399
00:24:54,627 --> 00:24:56,562
(Momoko) I'm sorry, Director, I didn't notice.

400
00:24:56,629 --> 00:25:01,067
>> What? It's not Momo-chan's fault, so it's okay.

401
00:25:01,133 --> 00:25:05,071
Mika-chan, you're fine today, so go home.

402
00:25:05,137 --> 00:25:07,073
(Mika) Yeah, but... >> Oh no.

403
00:25:07,139 --> 00:25:09,575
It's okay, it's okay, look. (Takuto) Director.

404
00:25:09,642 --> 00:25:11,577
They say it's not good to be so violent. >> Yes.

405
00:25:11,644 --> 00:25:13,579
Please rest for today. >> Yes.

406
00:25:13,646 --> 00:25:15,581
Did you understand? >> Yes.

407
00:25:15,648 --> 00:25:18,084
I was really worried. >> Yes.

408
00:25:18,150 --> 00:25:20,086
(Takuto) Can I have a moment?

409
00:25:20,152 --> 00:25:21,654
(Momoko) Yes.

410
00:25:24,657 --> 00:25:27,593
(Mika) Huh? Minseok-san also came home early.

411
00:25:27,660 --> 00:25:29,595
(Minseok) Ah.

412
00:25:29,662 --> 00:25:32,598
I'm with the director today.

413
00:25:32,665 --> 00:25:34,600
Oh, would you like some water?

414
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:36,602
>> Yes, thank you.

415
00:25:39,105 --> 00:25:43,109
(Takuto) I saw it on the director's desk.

416
00:25:44,610 --> 00:25:46,612
this.

417
00:25:50,616 --> 00:25:52,551
(Takuto) From the bank.

418
00:25:52,618 --> 00:25:56,055
I think this is a reminder to repay the loan to the clinic.

419
00:25:56,122 --> 00:25:58,557
Recently, the number of chronic patients has increased →

420
00:25:58,624 --> 00:26:03,563
I think the management was tough because the number of clinic points didn't increase.

421
00:26:03,629 --> 00:26:07,066
(Momoko) Director: When it comes to money, it's okay →

422
00:26:07,133 --> 00:26:09,568
Not a word like this...

423
00:26:09,635 --> 00:26:12,638
(Takuto) I guess he didn't want to worry everyone.

424
00:26:16,842 --> 00:26:20,279
(Kazami) I'm sorry today.

425
00:26:20,346 --> 00:26:23,783
(Minseok) No, I don't have anything.

426
00:26:23,849 --> 00:26:28,287
>> You interrupted our date.

427
00:26:28,354 --> 00:26:30,289
(Minseok) Eh.

428
00:26:30,356 --> 00:26:32,291
>> Me →

429
00:26:32,358 --> 00:26:36,796
He's a sharp person when it comes to things like that.

430
00:26:36,862 --> 00:26:38,864
Is that surprising?

431
00:26:40,366 --> 00:26:44,870
Doctors can understand other people very well.

432
00:26:47,873 --> 00:26:52,812
But I don't really understand myself.

433
00:26:52,878 --> 00:26:57,316
Both mind and body→

434
00:26:57,383 --> 00:27:02,321
I thought I knew →

435
00:27:02,388 --> 00:27:06,392
Sometimes I put others first.

436
00:27:09,895 --> 00:27:13,899
Whatever you want to say, that's it.

437
00:27:18,404 --> 00:27:22,341
Momo-chan...

438
00:27:22,408 --> 00:27:24,410
Nice to meet you.

439
00:27:26,912 --> 00:27:28,914
(Minseok) Yes.

440
00:27:33,419 --> 00:27:34,854
(sound of door opening)

441
00:27:37,156 --> 00:27:39,992
Korean

442
00:28:53,265 --> 00:28:54,633
(Kazami) But→

443
00:28:54,700 --> 00:28:58,637
Are you sure you won't cause trouble for Takuto?

444
00:28:58,704 --> 00:29:00,639
(Takuto) I'll convince my father.

445
00:29:01,307 --> 00:29:04,743
There is talk of making Kazami Clinic our satellite hospital →

446
00:29:04,810 --> 00:29:08,747
This has been brought up before, so it should be easy to understand.

447
00:29:08,814 --> 00:29:11,250
>> I see.

448
00:29:11,317 --> 00:29:16,255
In order to continue here, we need to think about management →

449
00:29:16,322 --> 00:29:22,261
One option might be to rely on Yamashiro Hospital.

450
00:29:22,328 --> 00:29:24,263
(Momoko) But, director.

451
00:29:24,330 --> 00:29:30,769
>> Even if we think about the future, the clinic will remain in the red →

452
00:29:30,836 --> 00:29:35,708
I can't leave Momo-chan alone.

453
00:29:35,775 --> 00:29:39,778
(Momoko) That's about me... (Sound of door opening and closing)

454
00:29:42,281 --> 00:29:44,216
(Minseok) I just returned home.

455
00:29:44,283 --> 00:29:46,719
>> Welcome back, Minseok-kun. (Takuto) Hey!

456
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:49,722
(Minseok) Director: Are you okay now?

457
00:29:49,788 --> 00:29:52,725
>> Yeah, I just had a slight arrhythmia.

458
00:29:52,791 --> 00:29:55,227
Sorry for making you worry.

459
00:29:55,294 --> 00:29:57,296
(Minseok) Ah, no.

460
00:30:02,801 --> 00:30:05,237
(Minseok) Is that so?

461
00:30:05,304 --> 00:30:09,808
(Momoko) I really appreciate Takuto's offer, but...

462
00:30:13,813 --> 00:30:16,315
(Minseok) Are you stuck on something?

463
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:21,253
(Momoko) Actually, it happened before.

464
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:26,759
I'm talking about turning the clinic into a satellite hospital with Takuto.

465
00:30:26,825 --> 00:30:30,262
(Minseok) Did it not go well?

466
00:30:30,329 --> 00:30:34,266
(Momoko) Takuto's father is also a doctor →

467
00:30:34,333 --> 00:30:37,703
I guess he's a shrewd manager.

468
00:30:37,770 --> 00:30:41,207
I was trying to change the management of the clinic.

469
00:30:41,273 --> 00:30:43,209
Of course, as a doctor →

470
00:30:43,275 --> 00:30:45,711
This was done in order to protect medical care.

471
00:30:45,778 --> 00:30:50,216
But the space for the children's cafeteria is also →

472
00:30:50,282 --> 00:30:53,786
They said it would be better to use it as a hospital facility.

473
00:30:55,788 --> 00:31:00,226
Accepting all patients in need as before →

474
00:31:00,292 --> 00:31:03,229
It seemed like it would be difficult →

475
00:31:03,295 --> 00:31:07,233
The director refused.

476
00:31:07,299 --> 00:31:10,236
So if→

477
00:31:10,302 --> 00:31:14,740
As this story progresses...

478
00:31:14,807 --> 00:31:19,812
(Minseok) It may become impossible to maintain a place where everyone can feel safe.

479
00:31:21,313 --> 00:31:24,250
Momoko's dream.

480
00:31:24,316 --> 00:31:27,253
(Momoko) Even if you say that →

481
00:31:27,319 --> 00:31:30,756
I can't leave it like this.

482
00:31:30,823 --> 00:31:33,826
I'd be in trouble if something happened to the director.

483
00:31:37,263 --> 00:31:40,199
(Momoko) Ah, I've arrived.

484
00:31:40,266 --> 00:31:42,701
(Minseok) We have arrived.

485
00:31:42,768 --> 00:31:45,204
(Momoko) I don't have to arrive.

486
00:31:45,271 --> 00:31:57,216
♪～

487
00:31:57,283 --> 00:32:02,221
(Minseok) I'll see if I can do something too.

488
00:32:02,288 --> 00:32:04,290
(Momoko) Yes.

489
00:32:08,294 --> 00:32:10,229
(Minseok) Did you forget?

490
00:32:10,296 --> 00:32:13,299
A spell to cheer you up.

491
00:32:15,801 --> 00:32:20,806
(2 people) ``There is no tree that will not fall down even if you cut it 10 times.''

492
00:32:30,649 --> 00:32:33,719
(Minseok) It's on the right. >> Thank you very much.

493
00:32:33,786 --> 00:32:35,788
(Minseok) Please take your time.

494
00:32:41,727 --> 00:32:45,664
(Mizushima) Sigh. Today is also full of inbound customers.

495
00:32:45,731 --> 00:32:47,666
(Natsume) The day goes by so quickly.

496
00:32:47,733 --> 00:32:49,668
(Minseok) Thank you for your hard work. (Natsume) Thank you for your hard work.

497
00:32:49,735 --> 00:32:54,173
But if you think about those days, it's a good story.

498
00:32:54,239 --> 00:32:56,175
Oh, is it coronavirus?

499
00:32:56,241 --> 00:32:59,678
I thought we were going out of business because we weren't getting any reservations.

500
00:32:59,745 --> 00:33:03,682
Every day I desperately search for and apply for grants and subsidies.

501
00:33:03,749 --> 00:33:06,685
I almost forgot that I was a hotelier.

502
00:33:06,752 --> 00:33:08,687
(Minseok) Subsidy.

503
00:33:08,754 --> 00:33:11,690
>> Ah hahahaha...｡

504
00:33:11,757 --> 00:33:16,695
The assistant manager doesn't know about the hardships we went through back then.

505
00:33:16,762 --> 00:33:19,198
Shall I tell you what?

506
00:33:19,264 --> 00:33:21,200
Yeah, after this...

507
00:33:21,266 --> 00:33:23,202
(Minseok) Sorry, please excuse me.

508
00:33:23,268 --> 00:33:25,270
thank you very much.

509
00:33:28,774 --> 00:33:30,776
>> I was dumped.

510
00:33:32,277 --> 00:33:35,214
I haven't invited you yet →

511
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:38,150
I can't say that I was dumped.

512
00:33:38,217 --> 00:33:39,651
yes.

513
00:33:39,718 --> 00:33:43,155
(Sound of keyboard hitting)

514
00:33:43,222 --> 00:33:44,723
(click sound)

515
00:33:47,726 --> 00:33:50,662
(click sound)

516
00:33:50,729 --> 00:33:54,733
(Minseok) ``Subsidy for private medical institutions.''

517
00:34:00,239 --> 00:34:02,174
(click sound)

518
00:34:02,241 --> 00:34:05,177
(Patient) Doctor. (Momoko) Yes.

519
00:34:05,244 --> 00:34:08,180
>> This place won't disappear, right?

520
00:34:08,247 --> 00:34:10,182
(Momoko) Huh?

521
00:34:10,249 --> 00:34:12,684
(Patient) Director: Are you feeling unwell?

522
00:34:12,751 --> 00:34:15,687
Then I think I'll close this place →

523
00:34:15,754 --> 00:34:17,689
Everyone.

524
00:34:17,756 --> 00:34:21,693
Just because there is a clinic nearby →

525
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:26,265
Everyone in the area was so reassuring.

526
00:34:31,270 --> 00:34:33,705
(Momoko) It's okay, don't worry.

527
00:34:33,772 --> 00:34:36,208
Let's get your elbow healed sooner than later.

528
00:34:36,275 --> 00:34:38,277
>> Yes. (Momoko) Yes.

529
00:34:39,778 --> 00:34:42,214
(Salesperson) Yes, welcome.

530
00:34:42,281 --> 00:34:44,216
(Takuto) Yo!

531
00:34:44,283 --> 00:34:46,218
>> Ah hahaha.

532
00:34:46,285 --> 00:34:48,220
(Takuto) Good work. >> Good work.

533
00:34:48,287 --> 00:34:50,722
(Takuto) Ah, can I live? >> Yeah. (Takuto) Well then, two servings.

534
00:34:50,789 --> 00:34:52,724
(Salesperson) Yes.

535
00:34:52,791 --> 00:34:56,228
Ah~ I'm tired! (Takuto) I mean, what happened?

536
00:34:56,295 --> 00:34:58,730
Isn't it unusual for Anzu to suddenly invite you out?

537
00:34:58,797 --> 00:35:01,733
>> I thought Taku-chan might be feeling lonely.

538
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:05,237
(Takuto) Me? Me with 250,000 followers?

539
00:35:05,304 --> 00:35:07,239
>> Even if you have a lot of followers, be an important person →

540
00:35:07,306 --> 00:35:09,308
You're not being followed.

541
00:35:11,810 --> 00:35:15,314
(Takuto) What is this? I can't do it.

542
00:35:28,827 --> 00:35:30,829
(knock)

543
00:35:33,832 --> 00:35:35,834
(Momoko) Yes.

544
00:35:45,777 --> 00:35:47,779
(Momoko) Yeah.

545
00:35:51,783 --> 00:35:54,219
(Takuto) Even I know that.

546
00:35:54,286 --> 00:35:56,722
I missed the timing.

547
00:35:56,788 --> 00:35:58,223
>> Huh?

548
00:35:58,290 --> 00:36:02,227
(Takuto) 23 years. 23 years.

549
00:36:02,294 --> 00:36:05,230
I wonder if my turn will come someday.

550
00:36:05,297 --> 00:36:07,733
But...

551
00:36:07,799 --> 00:36:09,234
He didn't come.

552
00:36:09,301 --> 00:36:11,236
>> Didn't you come?

553
00:36:11,303 --> 00:36:13,238
(Takuto) I am, I am →

554
00:36:13,305 --> 00:36:17,242
I've lived my life thinking that I'm the main character in a drama.

555
00:36:17,309 --> 00:36:21,747
He's a doctor, a childhood friend, and even has a nice personality.

556
00:36:21,813 --> 00:36:23,749
No matter how you look at it, he's the main character.

557
00:36:23,815 --> 00:36:27,252
>> That's right! (Takuto) But what...?

558
00:36:27,319 --> 00:36:31,256
As a son of a wealthy family, there is a bit of a shadow →

559
00:36:31,323 --> 00:36:35,260
There's a guy who even has a fateful episode with Momoko.

560
00:36:35,327 --> 00:36:37,696
>> Completely lose.

561
00:36:37,763 --> 00:36:40,198
(Takuto) But he's a good guy.

562
00:36:40,265 --> 00:36:42,200
>> Good face too.

563
00:36:42,267 --> 00:36:44,202
(Takuto) Even I would fall in love with something like that.

564
00:36:44,269 --> 00:36:46,271
>> It's a violation!

565
00:36:52,277 --> 00:36:54,279
But I don't understand.

566
00:36:56,281 --> 00:36:58,283
I don't understand.

567
00:37:02,788 --> 00:37:06,291
(Kyoko's voice) Will Momoko be able to be happy?

568
00:37:10,295 --> 00:37:15,801
I'm fine with it as long as Momoko is happy.

569
00:37:40,926 --> 00:37:43,462
(Minseok) Momoko-san.

570
00:37:43,528 --> 00:37:47,466
What happened? Until this time.

571
00:37:47,799 --> 00:37:50,802
(Momoko) I want to talk to you for a while.

572
00:37:59,811 --> 00:38:01,813
(Minseok) Did something happen?

573
00:38:04,816 --> 00:38:10,255
(Momoko) With the help of Takuto and this clinic, →

574
00:38:10,322 --> 00:38:12,758
I think I'll rebuild it.

575
00:38:14,259 --> 00:38:15,761
(Minseok) Huh?

576
00:38:17,262 --> 00:38:20,198
(Momoko) The director also says that's the best thing.

577
00:38:20,265 --> 00:38:24,770
(Minseok) But what about Momoko's dream?

578
00:38:26,271 --> 00:38:31,777
(Momoko) My dream is that clinics never disappear.

579
00:38:34,780 --> 00:38:38,717
(Minseok) The children's cafeteria will remain the same as before →

580
00:38:38,784 --> 00:38:41,720
Accepting patients in need →

581
00:38:41,787 --> 00:38:43,789
It's going to be difficult.

582
00:38:52,297 --> 00:38:54,733
(Momoko) Minseok-san→

583
00:38:54,800 --> 00:38:57,803
I'm not a medical professional so I wouldn't know.

584
00:39:00,305 --> 00:39:01,740
(Minseok) Eh.

585
00:39:01,807 --> 00:39:04,743
(Momoko) To protect the clinic →

586
00:39:04,810 --> 00:39:10,749
Sometimes things need to change, and not all of them are bad.

587
00:39:13,752 --> 00:39:16,688
(Minseok) Did something happen?

588
00:39:16,755 --> 00:39:22,761
(Momoko) I think now is an important time for my work.

589
00:39:26,264 --> 00:39:30,202
(Momoko) That's why...

590
00:39:30,268 --> 00:39:32,771
I don't want to be distracted by other things.

591
00:39:34,773 --> 00:39:36,775
(Minseok) What do you mean?

592
00:39:42,781 --> 00:39:44,783
(Momoko) Let's say goodbye.

593
00:39:48,787 --> 00:39:51,723
(Momoko) I'm sorry.

594
00:39:51,790 --> 00:39:54,292
I really want to break up with you.

595
00:39:58,296 --> 00:40:01,233
(Minseok) Wait a minute.

596
00:40:01,299 --> 00:40:06,805
Is that really what Momoko thinks?

597
00:40:11,243 --> 00:40:13,178
(Momoko) That's right.

598
00:40:13,245 --> 00:40:16,181
(Minseok) I am →

599
00:40:16,248 --> 00:40:20,185
I want to be close to Momoko-san when she is in trouble.

600
00:40:20,252 --> 00:40:26,191
When I'm worried, I want to be by your side to think of a solution together.

601
00:40:26,258 --> 00:40:30,695
(Momoko) I hate myself for neglecting love.

602
00:40:30,762 --> 00:40:33,698
And when Minseok was around →

603
00:40:33,765 --> 00:40:36,201
The problem won't be solved.

604
00:40:36,268 --> 00:40:39,204
I've always been the type of person who can do my best alone in times like this.

605
00:40:39,271 --> 00:40:42,207
(Minseok) Momoko-san. (Momoko) I want to concentrate.

606
00:40:42,274 --> 00:40:46,278
To my work and dreams.

607
00:40:49,781 --> 00:40:51,783
(Minseok) Don't lie.

608
00:40:55,287 --> 00:41:00,225
(Momoko) Minseok is also doing what he wants to do →

609
00:41:00,292 --> 00:41:03,728
I think you should think about it more seriously.

610
00:41:03,795 --> 00:41:06,731
(Minseok) Huh?

611
00:41:06,798 --> 00:41:10,235
(Momoko) Something...

612
00:41:10,302 --> 00:41:16,675
I guess that means the heir hasn't left yet.

613
00:41:16,741 --> 00:41:19,678
It's sweet.

614
00:41:19,744 --> 00:41:23,181
If there is a hotel you really want to build →

615
00:41:23,248 --> 00:41:26,251
You know it has to stay like this.

616
00:41:30,255 --> 00:41:36,194
(Momoko) There are trees that won't fall even if you cut them 10 times.

617
00:41:36,261 --> 00:41:39,197
Not everything will go as planned.

618
00:41:39,264 --> 00:41:51,776
♪～

619
00:42:08,793 --> 00:42:10,228
(Momoko) [Eh]

620
00:42:10,295 --> 00:42:13,798
>> [Could I talk to you for a moment? ]

621
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:17,302
(Momoko) [Yes]

622
00:42:24,809 --> 00:42:27,312
>> [I apologize for the inconvenience, but I have a request to make]

623
00:42:30,315 --> 00:42:33,752
[Please break up with Minseok]

624
00:42:33,818 --> 00:42:36,755
(Momoko) [Eh...]

625
00:42:36,821 --> 00:42:40,759
[Um… wait a minute…]

626
00:42:40,825 --> 00:42:44,763
>> [His mother closed down a hotel in Tokyo→

627
00:42:44,829 --> 00:42:47,265
I am planning to cut Minseok together.]

628
00:42:47,332 --> 00:42:48,767
(Momoko) [Eh? ]

629
00:42:48,833 --> 00:42:52,837
>> [He will lose his favorite hotel job]

630
00:42:56,841 --> 00:43:02,280
(Momoko) [That means that Minseok and I will break up →

631
00:43:02,347 --> 00:43:04,783
How are you related? ]

632
00:43:04,849 --> 00:43:07,285
>> [I...→

633
00:43:07,352 --> 00:43:13,224
Shinkai Group is ready to accept him as a son-in-law.]

634
00:43:13,291 --> 00:43:15,226
(Momoko) [Eh? ]

635
00:43:15,293 --> 00:43:20,231
>> [If you marry me, you will be in charge of managing our hotel in the future]

636
00:43:20,298 --> 00:43:24,736
[I can protect his precious future]

637
00:43:24,803 --> 00:43:27,739
(Momoko) [But that's not it...]

638
00:43:27,806 --> 00:43:30,241
>> [I was told that I would be cut from Hwangeum Group→

639
00:43:30,308 --> 00:43:32,811
Do you know what I mean? ]

640
00:43:35,313 --> 00:43:37,248
(Momoko) [No]

641
00:43:37,315 --> 00:43:40,251
>> [If I get kicked out of my family's major fandom →

642
00:43:40,318 --> 00:43:42,754
Minseok has been rumored to have strange rumors →

643
00:43:42,821 --> 00:43:45,824
It will be difficult to work in the hotel industry.]

644
00:43:48,326 --> 00:43:50,762
(Momoko) [Like that...]

645
00:43:50,829 --> 00:43:54,265
>> [For me →

646
00:43:54,332 --> 00:43:57,335
I can protect him.]

647
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:05,276
〔please〕

648
00:44:05,343 --> 00:44:07,846
[Please break up with him]

649
00:44:11,783 --> 00:44:31,736
♪～

650
00:44:31,803 --> 00:44:37,242
(Momoko) [Such a dream must never come true]

651
00:44:37,308 --> 00:44:39,244
(Minseok) [Yes]

652
00:44:39,310 --> 00:45:00,765
♪～

653
00:45:00,832 --> 00:45:06,771
(Momoko) [I want to protect the clinic as a place where someone can feel safe.]

654
00:45:06,838 --> 00:45:08,773
(Minseok) [Are you dreaming? ]

655
00:45:08,840 --> 00:45:10,708
(Momoko) [It's a dream]

656
00:45:10,775 --> 00:45:13,712
(Minseok) [Character to cheer up]

657
00:45:13,778 --> 00:45:18,216
(2 people) [“There is no tree that will not fall even after being cut 10 times”]

658
00:45:18,283 --> 00:45:28,726
♪～

659
00:45:28,793 --> 00:45:30,795
\Minseok-san/

660
00:45:37,302 --> 00:45:39,304
(Minseok) Inri-san.

661
00:45:46,311 --> 00:45:48,246
>> I have something to tell you.

662
00:45:48,313 --> 00:46:00,325
♪～
